com.radiusnetworks.util

Class MissingKeyException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • java.lang.RuntimeException
          • java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
            • com.radiusnetworks.util.MissingKeyException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public final class MissingKeyException
extends IllegalArgumentException
    A MissingKeyException may be thrown when a method is invoked with a map argument which does not contain an expected or required key.

    This is an alternative to a NullPointerException. A MissingKeyException states more specifically that it was a key that was null (i.e. not set) - instead of the value or the map itself.

    Since:
    0.6.0
    See Also:
    IllegalArgumentException, MissingValueException, Serialized Form
